Defines a test case with an optional set of tags.
```cpp
TEST_CASE("vectors can be sized and resized") {
    std::vector<int> v(5);
    REQUIRE(v.size() == 5);
}

TEST_CASE("math operations" * doctest::test_suite("math")) {
    CHECK(1 + 1 == 2);
}
```

Defines a sub-section within a test case. Subcases share setup code and each runs independently.
```cpp
TEST_CASE("subcases") {
    int x = 0;
    SUBCASE("increment") { x++; CHECK(x == 1); }
    SUBCASE("decrement") { x--; CHECK(x == -1); }
}
```

Evaluates `expression` and reports failure if false, but continues execution.
```cpp
CHECK(x == 42);
CHECK(result.has_value());
CHECK(str == "expected");
```

Evaluates `expression` and aborts the test case if false.
```cpp
REQUIRE(ptr != nullptr);
REQUIRE(vec.size() > 0);
```

Evaluates `expression` and issues a warning if false, but does not fail the test.
```cpp
WARN(performance_ms < 100);
WARN(deprecated_count == 0);
```

Checks that `lhs` equals `rhs`. Continues on failure.
```cpp
CHECK_EQ(result, 42);
CHECK_EQ(str, "hello");
```

Checks that `lhs` is not equal to `rhs`.
```cpp
CHECK_NE(ptr, nullptr);
CHECK_NE(result, -1);
```

Checks that `lhs` is less than `rhs`.
```cpp
CHECK_LT(elapsed_ms, 1000);
CHECK_LT(error_count, max_errors);
```

Checks that evaluating `expression` throws an exception.
```cpp
CHECK_THROWS(throw_func());
CHECK_THROWS(parse(""));
```

Checks that `expression` throws a specific exception type.
```cpp
CHECK_THROWS_AS(parse("bad"), std::runtime_error);
CHECK_THROWS_AS(divide(1, 0), DivisionByZero);
```
